The paper proposes a new type of neural network for generating high-dimensional discrete data, such as binary vectors, categorical data, natural language, and network log files. This falls under the category of machine learning and artificial intelligence, specifically in the sub-fields of deep learning (cs.LG), natural language processing (cs.CL), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of stochastic gradient descent and Markov-chain Monte Carlo methods, which are commonly used in neural network optimization and training, respectively, and are relevant to the sub-fields of neural networks (cs.NE) and computer vision (cs.CV).
